g.text: The data is related with direct marketing campaigns (phone calls).
Bank client's features : Age, Job, Marital, Education, Default(has credit in default), Housing, Loan.
Contact with client features : Contact, Month, Day of week, Duration.
Aim : Has the client subscribed a term deposit? (yes / no)
we will find the best model by confusion matrix with the lowest False Positive as possible.
False Positive, means the client do not subscribed to term deposit, but the model thinks he did. It is harmful, because we
think that we already have that client but we dont.
Best Model is K Nearest Neighbors (knn) with Accuracy = 91% and False Positive Rate = 1.5%
converting categorical variables into numerical variables
